           SPELL=devilspie
         VERSION=0.20.1
          SOURCE=${SPELL}-${VERSION}.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}-${VERSION}
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.burtonini.com/computing/${SOURCE}
        WEB_SITE=http://www.burtonini.com/blog/computers/devilspie
         ENTERED=20040618
      SOURCE_GPG=gurus.gpg:${SOURCE}.sig
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
           SHORT="A window matching utility"
cat << EOF
Devil's Pie can be configured to detect windows as they are created, and match
the windows to a set of rules. If the window matches the rules, actions are
applied to it. For example XChat can be put on all desktops by default or Aterm
can be ripped of decorations by default (tested in OpenBox).
EOF
